-- Bernanke Says ‘We’re Not Engaged in a Currency War’
-- B y   J o s h u a   Z u m b r u n
-- 2013-02-26T16:21:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-26/bernanke-says-we-re-not-engaged-in-a-currency-war-.html
Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S.
Bernanke  said the central bank’s easing policies benefit U.S.
trading partners by boosting global growth and denied that it is
seeking to weaken the dollar.  “We are not engaged in a currency war,” Bernanke said
today in response to a question during testimony to the Senate
Banking Committee in Washington.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joshua Zumbrun in Washington at 
 jzumbrun@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
